OL,3,CHousehold water bills set to rise by
OL,4,C#19 a year
OL,6,FMike Keil, chief executive of the
OL,7,FConsumer Council for Water (CCW),
OL,8,Fsaid: "Millions of people will feel
OL,9,Fupset and anxious at the prospect of
OL,10,Fthese water bill rises and question
OL,11,Fthe fairness of them given some water
OL,12,Fcompanies' track record of failure and
OL,13,Fpoor service.
OL,15,F"We estimate about two million
OL,16,Fhouseholds in England and Wales
OL,17,Fcurrently cannot afford their water
OL,18,Fbill and, while the increase in
OL,19,Ffinancial assistance is welcome, it
OL,20,Ffalls short of what is needed."
